DANIEL [O VER MACHINE]:
<i>Hi, it's Daniel.</i>

1626
01:52:33,444 --> 01:52:37,740
<i>Remember what I said in the restaurant?</i>
<i>Well, please forget it word by word.</i>

1627
01:52:39,178 --> 01:52:41,541
<i>They're gonna build</i>
<i>a new Yankee stadium.</i>

1628
01:52:42,410 --> 01:52:45,774
<i>I don't know why I said that.</i>
<i>I'm making small talk. I hate small talk.</i>

1629
01:52:45,944 --> 01:52:50,377
<i>I hate the people who make small talk.</i>
<i>I should... I should stop. I'm stopping.</i>

1630
01:52:50,544 --> 01:52:51,532
<i>Shit!</i>

1631
01:52:51,710 --> 01:52:53,199
[HANGS UP]

1632
01:53:03,044 --> 01:53:04,635
Gerry?

1633
01:53:09,011 --> 01:53:09,999
[FOOTSTEPS]

1634
01:53:10,178 --> 01:53:13,008
DANIEL:
My uncle can get us in anytime we want.

1635
01:53:13,678 --> 01:53:15,837
He turned the lights on for us.

1636
01:53:18,445 --> 01:53:20,274
HOLLY:
It's <i>amazing...</i>

1637
01:53:47,778 --> 01:53:49,142
You sure?

1638
01:53:51,179 --> 01:53:52,906
It's okay.

1639
01:53:54,611 --> 01:53:58,169
DANIEL:
"Dear Holly, I don't have much time.

1640
01:53:58,579 --> 01:54:03,511
I don't mean literally, I mean, you're out
buying ice cream and you'll be home soon...

1641
01:54:03,912 --> 01:54:06,435
...but I have a feeling this is the last letter.

1642
01:54:06,612 --> 01:54:09,203
Because there's only one thing
left to tell you.

1643
01:54:09,779 --> 01:54:12,836
It isn't to go down memory lane
or make you buy a lamp.

1644
01:54:13,012 --> 01:54:16,172
You can take care of yourself
without any help from me.

1645
01:54:17,312 --> 01:54:22,176
It's to tell you how much you move me.
How you changed me.

1646
01:54:22,946 --> 01:54:26,275
You made me a man
by loving me, Holly...

1647
01:54:26,446 --> 01:54:30,038
...and for that I am eternally grateful.

1648
01:54:30,212 --> 01:54:31,610
Literally.

1649
01:54:32,846 --> 01:54:37,176
If you can promise me anything,
promise me that whenever you're sad...

1650
01:54:37,345 --> 01:54:38,743
<i>: : :or unsure: : :

1651
01:54:39,412 --> 01:54:41,742
...or you lose complete faith...

1652
01:54:42,512 --> 01:54:45,445
...that you'll try and see yourself
through my eyes.

1653
01:54:45,946 --> 01:54:48,844
Thank you for the honor
of being my wife.

1654
01:54:49,046 --> 01:54:51,342
I'm a man with no regrets.

1655
01:54:51,513 --> 01:54:53,035
How lucky am I?

1656
01:54:54,413 --> 01:54:59,072
You made my life, Holly,
but I'm just one chapter in yours.

1657
01:54:59,447 --> 01:55:01,208
There'll be more.

1658
01:55:01,680 --> 01:55:03,168
I promise.

1659
01:55:04,180 --> 01:55:07,237
So here it comes, the big one.

1660
01:55:09,180 --> 01:55:11,271
Don't be afraid to fall in love again.

1661
01:55:12,880 --> 01:55:16,676
Watch out for that signal
when life as you know it ends.

1662
01:55:18,980 --> 01:55:23,412
P.S., I will always love you."

1663
01:55:43,880 --> 01:55:46,278
Have you thought about this?

1664
01:55:47,448 --> 01:55:49,675
About me, I mean?

1665
01:55:51,847 --> 01:55:53,507
Have you?

1666
01:55:56,581 --> 01:55:58,206
Yeah.

1667
01:56:23,881 --> 01:56:26,143
- This isn't gonna work, is it?
- No way, no how!

1668
01:56:26,314 --> 01:56:27,473
- Damn!
- Oh!

1669
01:56:27,748 --> 01:56:29,509
[LAUGHING]

1670
01:56:29,714 --> 01:56:31,340
Oh, wow.

1671
01:56:31,748 --> 01:56:34,237
I mean, that was like kissing my sister.

1672
01:56:34,415 --> 01:56:37,074
- I'm so relieved!
- Ha-ha-ha.

1673
01:56:37,248 --> 01:56:40,805
I got this letter and I thought he must have
been feeling self-sacrificing...

1674
01:56:40,981 --> 01:56:43,970
...but he's really full of crap.
If he meant it, he'd give me a sign.

1675
01:56:44,148 --> 01:56:47,376
- I hate signs.
- Then I got your message on the machine.

1676
01:56:47,649 --> 01:56:49,046
[SIGHS]

1677
01:56:53,915 --> 01:56:56,643
Weird, bitter friends?

1678
01:56:58,415 --> 01:57:00,176
Forever.

1679
01:57:00,816 --> 01:57:02,247
[SIGHS]

1680
01:57:12,282 --> 01:57:14,044
What's wrong, friend?

1681
01:57:14,215 --> 01:57:16,182
It's Gerry.

1682
01:57:18,183 --> 01:57:20,012
It's been a year...

1683
01:57:22,348 --> 01:57:25,213
...and I don't feel him
around me anymore.

1684
01:57:27,216 --> 01:57:29,511
I don't think he's here anymore.

1685
01:57:32,016 --> 01:57:34,209
I think Gerry's gone.

1686
01:57:35,749 --> 01:57:37,375
[WHISPERS]
He's really gone.

1687
01:57:56,616 --> 01:57:59,047
HOLLY:
<i>Dear Gerry, you said you wanted me...</i>

1688
01:57:59,216 --> 01:58:00,648
<i>... to fall in love again...</i>

1689
01:58:00,817 --> 01:58:05,215
<i>... and maybe one day I will,</i>
<i>but there are all kinds of love out there.</i>

1690
01:58:06,416 --> 01:58:08,211
<i>This is my one and only life...</i>

1691
01:58:08,616 --> 01:58:12,071
<i>... and it's a great and terrible</i>
<i>and short and endless thing...</i>

1692
01:58:12,249 --> 01:58:15,045
<i>... and none of us come out of it alive.</i>

1693
01:58:24,883 --> 01:58:29,509
<i>I don't have a plan except</i>
<i>that it's time my mom laughed again.</i>

1694
01:58:29,716 --> 01:58:31,546
<i>She's never seen the world.</i>

1695
01:58:31,716 --> 01:58:37,706
<i>She's never seen Ireland, so I'm</i>
<i>taking her back to where we started.</i>

1696
01:58:43,950 --> 01:58:46,314
<i>Maybe now she'll understand.</i>

1697
01:58:54,851 --> 01:58:56,043
Mom?

1698
01:59:11,617 --> 01:59:12,810
William?

1699
01:59:14,717 --> 01:59:15,910
Hello, you.

1700
01:59:19,218 --> 01:59:20,581
You back for another visit?

1701
01:59:21,918 --> 01:59:23,214
How long?

1702
01:59:24,285 --> 01:59:25,841
I don't know.

1703
01:59:28,151 --> 01:59:30,515
Oh, um... This is my mom, Patricia.

1704
01:59:30,951 --> 01:59:32,814
Hello. This is me father, Patsy.

1705
01:59:37,051 --> 01:59:38,914
You've dropped your sweets, luv.

1706
01:59:39,085 --> 01:59:41,074
Mustn't do that around these parts.

1707
01:59:41,251 --> 01:59:44,843
Pretty woman like you,
a fella could take it the wrong way.

1708
01:59:45,351 --> 01:59:46,408
[LAUGHING]

1709
01:59:46,585 --> 01:59:48,574
[PATSY LAUGHING]

1710
02:00:02,819 --> 02:00:04,375
So I'll see you around, then?

1711
02:00:05,452 --> 02:00:06,884
Yeah.

1712
02:00:13,684 --> 02:00:17,582
HOLLY: <i>I don't know how you did it,</i>
<i>but you brought me back from the dead.</i>

1713
02:00:17,751 --> 02:00:19,774
<i>I'll write to you again soon.</i>

1714
02:00:19,951 --> 02:00:21,814
<i>P. S...</i>

1715
02:00:21,984 --> 02:00:23,643
[WHISPERS]
<i>Guess what.</i>

